## Limitations
The primary limitation of this report is the reliance on secondary sources, which may present varying interpretations of historical events. Additionally, the lack of precise archaeological evidence from the Indus Valley Civilization limits the ability to draw definitive conclusions about the early religious practices that contributed to Hinduism. Furthermore, the complexity and diversity of Hindu traditions make it challenging to encapsulate its origins in a single narrative.